name: bleaching and dyeing, yarn | bleaching and dyeing, yarn | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20140/documentation

This dataset covers all relevant input and output flows for bleaching and dyeing of 1 kg greige yarn as a service activity. The inventory is mainly based on industry data and is supplemented, where necessary, with secondary processing energy data from machinery manufacturers. The dataset is a weighted average of the respective datasets in India and Bangladesh.;;Bleaching:;This activity bleaches greige yarn. Bleaching improves whiteness by removing natural coloration and remaining trace impurities from the cotton; the degree of bleaching necessary is determined;by the required whiteness and absorbency. ;;;Dyeing:;This inventory is for dyeing 40/2 CW count greige yarn to the dye shade 18-309.;This activity is modeled as a service, so no input of yarn is considered.

The bleaching activity starts with loading the greige yarn into the dyeing machine. However, this activity is modeled as a service, so no input of greige yarn is considered in the inputs from technosphere.

This datasets ends with 1 kg of this service which has to be used with 1 kg of yarn. Drying is included.
